survey_response.review_text:
I got my baby delivered by doctor Harshika. 
I just walked in after having my ultra sound. But I must say it was perfect decision. This doctor never scared me regarding my pregnancy. She just gives sweet smile and says don't worry I am here and everything will be be smooth. Just take care of you and your diet.
I always wanted a normal delivery and at last I got my baby delivered normally.
It was such a homely experience in this hospital. 
Staff over here is very co operative. They really motivated me and were near me when I was in labour pain. At last I gave up but the nurses and staff they helped me to go through this journey.

Thankyou doctor Harshika for this good time with you.

review_reply.reply_text: Thank you Rashmi for your kind words. Wish you and your cute baby good luck.

survey_response.review_text: I got pregnant during the commencement of the lockdown period and was very nervous about it considering the circumstances and my history. However, immediately after the first consultation with Dr. Bavishi I felt markedly reassured. Thereafter throughout the course of the pregnancy Dr. Bavishi was extremely hands on and available at all points to make this a smooth journey. Specially her practical approach played a great hand in calming my nerves in various instances. A special note of thanks to the staff at the maternity home who have made my stay at the maternity home extremely comfortable experience.  Thanks to the efforts of Dr. Bavishi and her team I gave birth to a healthy boy. Highly recommend her and her maternity home.

I had been diagnosed with ectopic pregnancy through sonography at a nearby hospital. The case being too risky , the hospital insisted on emergency surgery. As this was the first surgery in my life, I was too scared being operated. I reached out to Dr Harshika Bavishi for advice. Dr. made me understand the procedure and the risks involved if we wait any longer. She did another sonography to assess the risks. She immediately contacted her assistant surgeon and anesthetist. I got operated at kolekar hospital in chembur .  Dr. Bavishi is  such a competent surgeon , the surgery went well without any complications. She took extra care in post surgery treatment. I was almost back on my feet just after 3 days of surgery. Her professional attitude as a surgeon and strict yet caring nature as a doctor made me feel really comfortable even for this critical surgery. I would strongly recommend Dr. Harshika Bavishi for any gynaec related issues.

She has a great vibe around her which makes everything seem so simple and easy. She didn't ask for unnecessary tests or requirement and tries to work on what is best for you. I did such a major surgery Hysterotomy with her and I am glad I chose her. I am really thankful we found Dr Harshika Bavishi. I couldn't ask for anyone better.

She has been my doctor since I was pregnant with my first child till now.

A very very very nice human being and an equally good doctor. Her treatment for my menopause is perfect and she has helped me through my tough times. 

Her treatment both with medicine and counseling for depression and pre-menopausal symptoms.

Dr. Harshika has been my doctor for last 23 years .
Very friendly n patient .clears all your doubts .
Woulndt think of any other doctor for my problems 
Always there personally in times of emergencies or complications which is vry rare nowadays .
Recommended any day for all ur gyneac problems

I have been consulting Dr. Harshika Bavishi since my childhood & all my ailments simce then till now have been very well diagnosed and treated with to the highest level of my mental satisfaction. I would personally recommend every woman / girl to seek her advice for all women related health issues. - Amrita Gupta

review_reply.reply_text:
Hi there, we are sorry that your consultation with Dr. Harshika did not go as per expectations. We try our best to answer most of our patient questions in a detailed fashion. However, given the nature of the practice, at times, the doctor may have a pending emergency/ situation to attend to. Nonetheless, you can be rest assured that the guidance you received, though short, is correct. 

As you may know, answers on Google are generic and based on incomplete knowledge, coming not necessarily from professionals . All people and bodies are different. Hence, what applies to one may not apply to another. We strongly recommend that you consult a professional doctor to understand what is right for your body and not rely on Google articles.

Planning a pregnancy is a matter of patience and a process. We believe in slow but steady progress with the least necessary medicines and tests needed. However, these right treatments require regular follow-ups. 

We hold the highest standards in patient satisfaction and appreciate your feedback. As this review is anonymous, we are not able to identify the case, consultation and hence the recommended course of action. Kindly do share your details to help us understand the cause of dissatisfaction and hence address it. 

Alternatively, we would be happy to address your concerns with another consultation (you may choose to do this online or in person).

We wish you the very best of health for your planned pregnancy.
